<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>MOR/RYDE RUBBER SPRING SUSPENSION - MAINTENANCE - U-BOLTS, LEVELING BOLT, OR AXLE PAD ADJUSTMENT SEAT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0300902" svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
        <title>U-BOLTS, LEVELING BOLT, OR AXLE PAD ADJUSTMENT SEAT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure vehicle is elevated and chassis is supported with safety stands, the front wheels
                blocked, and the suspension hanging unsupported.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten U-bolt nuts to 50 ft-lbs. (68 N&#8226;m) of initial torque.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten leveling bolt on side of beam assembly into axle pad adjustment seat that sits on
                top of axle. Tighten to 75 ft-lbs. (102 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten U-bolt nuts following tightening sequence (
                <hotlnk document="s03009_2.xml" xrefid="f0300902">Figure 2</hotlnk>) until final torque is achieved.
                Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s03009_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300901">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Torque values must be verified with a torque wrench.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
